{"word":"ἐπεμβαίνω","slug":"ἐπεμβαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπεμβαίνω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-εμβήσομαι</el>) (aor2 <el>-ενέβην</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to step</i> or <i>tread upon</i>, and in <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <i>to stand upon</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; sometimes <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to embark</i> on ship-board, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to trample upon</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>insultare</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>τῷ καιρῷ ἐπ.</el> <i>to take advantage of</i> the opportunity, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}